#
# MU configuration
#
# 30/08/2013
# @mariohct
#

1 - Wifi configuration.
$ wifi-menu
Select the desired wifi-network, answer each screen of the wifi-menu software

2 - Enable the wifi profile at boot time. Assuming the configured wifi network is called "Bla"
$ netctl enable wlan0-Bla

3 - Configure the email address and password
$ vim /home/pi/application.conf

4 - Check if the wifi is working properly after a reboot
$ reboot

5 - If wifi network is ok, configure mu-server to load at boot time
$ mv /root/bash_profile /root/.bash_profile




